 across a product.\n\n  Line 21: Don't create more tokens than you have distinct use cases. 4–6 values is usually enough.\n\n  Line 42: - **Token approach**: define a `duration-instant` (0ms or 1ms) override for all duration tokens under reduced-motion, applied globally\n\n  Line 44: - Define duration and easing values as CSS custom properties (or platform-equivalent tokens)\n\n  Line 47: - Include motion tokens in the design token export pipeline — they should live alongside color and spacing tokens\n\n  Line 55: - Start with fewer tokens and add only when a new use case genuinely doesn't fit existing values\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/ux-strategy/skills/content-strategy/SKILL.md:\n  Line 15: - Defines content types and their attributes (e.g. an \"article\" has: title, summary, body, author, tags, publish date)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-systems/README.md:\n  Line 2: Build, document, and maintain scalable design systems — from tokens and components to accessibility and theming.\n\n  Line 4: - **design-token** — Define and organize design tokens with naming conventions and usage guidance.\n\n  Line 7: - **naming-convention** — Establish naming convention systems for design elements, components, and tokens.\n\n  Line 12: - **motion-system** — Define a motion system with duration tokens, easing vocabulary, and reduced-motion handling.\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"DESIGN\\.md|PRODUCT\\.md|stitch|author|forward|tokens|Style Reference","time":{"start":1782488688111,"end":1782488688152}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06e777fc9d85760a016a3e9e6fc19c8191ad6c9aef90eb3150"}},"id":"prt_f049ae5c800