Create a Distinctive Component Entry\n\n  Line 332: ## 3. COMPONENT EXTRACTION CHECKLIST\n\n  Line 347: ## 4. \"USE:\" LINE REQUIREMENT\n\n  Line 351: ### Format\n\n  Line 359: ### Examples\n\n  Line 382: ### Why the \"Use:\" line matters\n\n  Line 392: ## 5. STATE MATRIX TEMPLATE\n\n  Line 396: ### State matrix format\n\n  Line 399: ### Component — Variant\n\n  Line 414: ### Which states apply to which components\n\n  Line 427: ### Documenting states you did NOT observe\n\n  Line 440: ## 6. DECISION LOGIC\n\n  Line 444: ### Feedback to the user: Dialog vs Toast vs Banner\n\n  Line 454: ### Content display: Card vs List Item vs Table Row\n\n  Line 464: ### Selection: Dropdown vs Radio vs Segmented Control\n\n  Line 473: ### Document these decision rules in the DESIGN.md when the system contains multiple components that serve overlapping purposes. Include them as a subsection under Components or as a dedicated \"Component Selection Guide\" section.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/writing_style_guide.md:\n  Line 17: # DESIGN.md Writing Style Guide\n\n  Line 25: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n  Line 40: ## 2. Banned Words\n\n  Line 59: ## 3. Header — Tagline Rules\n\n  Line 64: # <Brand or Domain> — Style Reference\n\n  Line 76: ### What the tagline is NOT\n\n  Line 83: ### What the tagline IS\n\n  Line 87: ### Example taglines\n\n  Line 95: ### Tagline test\n\n  Line 101: ## 4. Intro Paragraph\n\n  Line 109: ### Intro test\n\n  Line 115: ## 5. Key Characteristics Format\n\n  Line 125: ### Good key characteristics\n\n  Line 134: ### Bad key characteristics\n\n  Line 143: ### Quantity\n\n  Line 149: ## 6. Colour Naming (`## Tokens — Colors`)\n\n  Line 167: ### Good role clauses\n\n  Line 173: ### Bad role clauses\n\n  Line 181: ### The characterizing clause\n\n  Line 187: ## 7. Value Embedding\n\n  Line 191: ### The rule\n\n  Line 195: ### Good value embedding\n\n  Line 203: ### Bad value embedding\n\n  Line 217: ### Where values DO stand alone\n\n  Line 223: ## 8. Do's and Don'ts Quality\n\n  Line 227: ### Don'ts: The Counter-Intuitive Test\n\n  Line 236: ### Good Don'ts\n\n  Line 250: ### Bad Don'ts\n\n  Line 264: ### Do's: The Implementation Shortcut Test\n\n  Line 268: ### Good Do's\n\n  Line 280: ## 9. Agent Prompt Guide\n\n  Line 284: ### Requirements\n\n  Line 293: ### Good agent prompt\n\n  Line 299: ### Bad agent prompt\n\n  Line 305: ### Prompt coverage\n\n  Line 316: ## 10. Information Density\n\n  Line 318: ### The deletion test\n\n  Line 322: ### Banned transition phrases\n\n  Line 335: ### No restating tables\n\n  Line 339: ### Paragraph density target\n\n  Line 345: ## 11. Ten Good/Bad Writing Comparisons\n\n  Line 347: ### 1. Atmosphere Description\n\n  Line 359: ### 2. Color Description\n\n  Line 371: ### 3. Key Characteristics\n\n  Line 383: ### 4. Do Entry\n\n  Line 395: ### 5. Don't Entry\n\n  Line 407: ### 6. Component Documentation\n\n  Line 419: ### 7. Typography Note\n\n  Line 431: ### 8. Layout Description\n\n  Line 443: ### 9. Agent Prompt Guide\n\n  Line 455: ### 10. Section Opening\n\n  Line 467: ## 12. Shadow Philosophy Pattern\n\n  Line 471: ### Structure\n\n  Line 478: ### Example\n\n  Line 484: ## 13. Section Structure Checklist (v3 Style Reference)\n\n  Line 506: ## 14. Final Quality Gate\n\n  Line 528: ## 15. Comparative Framing Pattern\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"^#{1,3} ","time":{"start":1782489104050,"end":1782489104066}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0feb6c7d13e1a352016a3ea00f52bc8191bebf877578da0eae"}},"id":"prt_f04a13e940014QOOM9LrysNRxB","sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","messageID":"msg_f04a0f3f4001DHbgqhdud1s6kO"}}
