{"type":"text","timestamp":1782489239703,"sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","part":{"id":"prt_f04a31f12001YsfUFp7MATTxEa","messageID":"msg_f04a2fe41001Lu07HMnpBISTsh","sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","type":"text","text":"Current inventories show `interface` has the most references but no assets; `foundations`, `motion`, and `audit` each have five references and no assets; `md-generator` is reference-heavy with two assets. I’m reading each mode’s owned reference list to anchor the gap analysis against the live state.","time":{"start":1782489227026,"end":1782489239701},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_000a819dbc7a60d4016a3ea08aff548191ae76d95caeed5758","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782489239787,"sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Ij4K9s6tgIE2g9ZfXolbqbk6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md","offset":154,"limit":65},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n154: ## 5. REFERENCES\n155: \n156: ### Core References\n157: \n158: - [`references/design-process/design_principles.md`](references/design-process/design_principles.md) - Full guidance: grounding, design principles, the two-pass process with AI-default calibration, restraint and self-critique, and interface writing.\n159: - [`references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md`](references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md) - The objective quality floor (accessibility, motion, touch, responsive, forms, charts). Apply as the pass/fail gate after the direction is set.\n160: - [`references/design-grounding/design_inventory.md`](references/design-grounding/design_inventory.md) - How to use a real design system you own as either reuse-ground or the named default to critique against. Never a chooser.\n161: - [`references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md`](references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md) - How to read real-world shipped UI live via Mobbin or Refero (Code Mode) to name the real-world default and deviate from it. Critique-against only, one reference, never a chooser, never copied.\n162: - [`references/mcp-tooling/mobbin_tools.md`](references/mcp-tooling/mobbin_tools.md) - Mobbin MCP tool catalog (search_screens, search_flows): arguments, the verified Code Mode call convention, result shape, troubleshooting.\n163: - [`references/mcp-tooling/refero_tools.md`](references/mcp-tooling/refero_tools.md) - Refero MCP tool catalog (8 tools across styles, screens, flows): the styles-first model, call convention, result shape, troubleshooting.\n164: - [`references/design-process/variation_diversity.md`](references/design-process/variation_diversity.md) - The seed-of-thought debias for producing two or more directions at once: a committed seed picks a non-median start in the grounded option space, the rest are spread to be distinct, and grounding plus the anti-default critique stay primary. Consult only when more than one direction is requested.\n165: - [`references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md`](references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md) - The real-UI loop: ground in a design system, reuse before generating, check the real render against the quality floor, hand off cleanly. Consult when producing or iterating on real UI.\n166: - [`references/aesthetics/README.md`](references/aesthetics/README.md) - Illustrative grounding cues (brutalist, minimalist, soft, apple-bento) for naming a realized default to critique against. Subordinate to grounding and the anti-default critique, never a chooser, preset, or pick-a-vibe axis.\n167: - [`LICENSE.txt`](LICENSE.txt) - Apache-2.0 terms for the vendored Anthropic `frontend-design` base.\n168: \n169: ### Manual Testing Playbook\n170: \n171: Manual testing scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md` (root index) plus per-scenario files under `manual_testing_playbook/<NN>--<topic>/`. Validate structure with `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`; execute scenarios in a real session for behavioral verification.\n172: \n173: ### Reference Loading Notes\n174: \n175: - Load `design_principles.md` on every design task. It is the authority for palette, type, structure, motion, and copy.\n176: - Keep Section 2 (SMART ROUTING) as the single routing authority.\n177: - `references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md` is the objective quality-floor gate; apply it after the direction is set.\n178: - A real design system you own is an OPTIONAL source to ground in or to name the default to deviate from, never a required step and never a style chooser. `design_principles.md` stays the authority.\n179: - The `references/aesthetics/` cues are illustrative critique-against reference only: cite at most one to name a realized default at the critique step, subordinate to grounding, never surfaced as a chooser, preset, or pick-a-vibe axis. `real_ui_loop.md` Section 8 owns this guardrail.\n180: - When the Mobbin or Refero subscriptions are connected, they are an OPTIONAL real-world critique-against reference (via Code Mode) for naming the category default to deviate from, never a chooser and never copied. `references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md` owns the rules and `design_principles.md` stays the authority.\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n185: \n186: **A design is ready when:**\n187: - ✅ The subject, audience, and the page's single job are named.\n188: - ✅ A token system (color, type, layout, signature) exists and was critiqued against the AI-default looks.\n189: - ✅ Every color and type decision derives from the revised plan.\n190: - ✅ The signature element is the one bold move, and everything else is quiet.\n191: - ✅ The quality floor holds: responsive, visible focus, reduced motion respected.\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n196: \n197: ### Related Skills\n198: \n199: - **`sk-code`** owns implementation. This skill decides the look, and sk-code builds it to the detected web surface's standards and verifies it.\n200: - **`sk-code-review`** can audit the built UI against the standards sk-code enforces.\n201: - **`mcp-chrome-devtools`** drives a real browser to screenshot the build for the self-critique step.\n202: - **`mcp-figma`** is the sibling transport to Figma Desktop. This skill's judgment applies whenever a Figma read or export feeds a design decision.\n203: - **Mobbin and Refero** (via Code Mode, `mobbin.*` / `refero.*`) are optional real-world UI reference libraries for naming the category's real-world default so a design can deviate from it deliberately. Read live, one reference, never a chooser, never copied. `references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md` owns the discipline.\n204: \n205: ### Knowledge Base Dependencies\n206: \n207: **Required**: `references/design-process/design_principles.md`. **Conditional**: `sk-code` web-surface references for the target stack during implementation.\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n212: \n213: The router (Section 2) loads `references/design-process/design_principles.md` for every design task. Hand implementation to `sk-code`, use `mcp-chrome-devtools` for screenshot-based self-critique, and reach for `system-spec-kit` when the work needs packet documentation.\n214: \n215: Upstream: vendored from [anthropics/skills/skills/frontend-design](https://github.com/anthropics/skills/tree/main/skills/frontend-design) under Apache-2.0. `LICENSE.txt` carries the full terms.\n\n(End of file - total 215 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [`references/design-process/design_principles.md`](references/design-process/design_principles.md) - Full guidance: grounding, design principles, the two-pass process with AI-default calibration, restraint and self-critique, and interface writing.\n- [`references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md`](references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md) - The objective quality floor (accessibility, motion, touch, responsive, forms, charts). Apply as the pass/fail gate after the direction is set.\n- [`references/design-grounding/design_inventory.md`](references/design-grounding/design_inventory.md) - How to use a real design system you own as either reuse-ground or the named default to critique against. Never a chooser.\n- [`references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md`](references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md) - How to read real-world shipped UI live via Mobbin or Refero (Code Mode) to name the real-world default and deviate from it. Critique-against only, one reference, never a chooser, never copied.\n- [`references/mcp-tooling/mobbin_tools.md`](references/mcp-tooling/mobbin_tools.md) - Mobbin MCP tool catalog (search_screens, search_flows): arguments, the verified Code Mode call convention, result shape, troubleshooting.\n- [`references/mcp-tooling/refero_tools.md`](references/mcp-tooling/refero_tools.md) - Refero MCP tool catalog (8 tools across styles, screens, flows): the styles-first model, call convention, result shape, troubleshooting.\n- [`references/design-process/variation_diversity.md`](references/design-process/variation_diversity.md) - The seed-of-thought debias for producing two or more directions at once: a committed seed picks a non-median start in the grounded option space, the rest are spread to be distinct, and grounding plus the anti-default critique stay primary. Consult only when more than one direction is requested.\n- [`references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md`](references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md) - The real-UI loop: ground in a design system, reuse before generating, check the real render against the quality floor, hand off cleanly. Consult when producing or iterating on real UI.\n- [`references/aesthetics/README.md`](references/aesthetics/README.md) - Illustrative grounding cues (brutalist, minimalist, soft, apple-bento) for naming a realized default to critique against. Subordinate to grounding and the anti-default critique, never a chooser, preset, or pick-a-vibe axis.\n- [`LICENSE.txt`](LICENSE.txt) - Apache-2.0 terms for the vendored Anthropic `frontend-design` base.\n\n### Manual Testing Playbook\n\nManual testing scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md` (root index) plus per-scenario files under `manual_testing_playbook/<NN>--<topic>/`. Validate structure with `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`; execute scenarios in a real session for behavioral verification.\n\n### Reference Loading Notes","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md","text":"## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [`references/design-process/design_principles.md`](references/design-process/design_principles.md) - Full guidance: grounding, design principles, the two-pass process with AI-default calibration, restraint and self-critique, and interface writing.\n- [`references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md`](references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md) - The objective quality floor (accessibility, motion, touch, responsive, forms, charts). Apply as the pass/fail gate after the direction is set.\n- [`references/design-grounding/design_inventory.md`](references/design-grounding/design_inventory.md) - How to use a real design system you own as either reuse-ground or the named default to critique against. Never a chooser.\n- [`references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md`](references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md) - How to read real-world shipped UI live via Mobbin or Refero (Code Mode) to name the real-world default and deviate from it. Critique-against only, one reference, never a chooser, never copied.\n- [`references/mcp-tooling/mobbin_tools.md`](references/mcp-tooling/mobbin_tools.md) - Mobbin MCP tool catalog (search_screens, search_flows): arguments, the verified Code Mode call convention, result shape, troubleshooting.\n- [`references/mcp-tooling/refero_tools.md`](references/mcp-tooling/refero_tools.md) - Refero MCP tool catalog (8 tools across styles, screens, flows): the styles-first model, call convention, result shape, troubleshooting.\n- [`references/design-process/variation_diversity.md`](references/design-process/variation_diversity.md) - The seed-of-thought debias for producing two or more directions at once: a committed seed picks a non-median start in the grounded option space, the rest are spread to be distinct, and grounding plus the anti-default critique stay primary. Consult only when more than one direction is requested.\n- [`references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md`](references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md) - The real-UI loop: ground in a design system, reuse before generating, check the real render against the quality floor, hand off cleanly. Consult when producing or iterating on real UI.\n- [`references/aesthetics/README.md`](references/aesthetics/README.md) - Illustrative grounding cues (brutalist, minimalist, soft, apple-bento) for naming a realized default to critique against. Subordinate to grounding and the anti-default critique, never a chooser, preset, or pick-a-vibe axis.\n- [`LICENSE.txt`](LICENSE.txt) - Apache-2.0 terms for the vendored Anthropic `frontend-design` base.\n\n### Manual Testing Playbook\n\nManual testing scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md` (root index) plus per-scenario files under `manual_testing_playbook/<NN>--<topic>/`. Validate structure with `python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`; execute scenarios in a real session for behavioral verification.\n\n### Reference Loading Notes\n\n- Load `design_principles.md` on every design task. It is the authority for palette, type, structure, motion, and copy.\n- Keep Section 2 (SMART ROUTING) as the single routing authority.\n- `references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md` is the objective quality-floor gate; apply it after the direction is set.\n- A real design system you own is an OPTIONAL source to ground in or to name the default to deviate from, never a required step and never a style chooser. `design_principles.md` stays the authority.\n- The `references/aesthetics/` cues are illustrative critique-against reference only: cite at most one to name a realized default at the critique step, subordinate to grounding, never surfaced as a chooser, preset, or pick-a-vibe axis. `real_ui_loop.md` Section 8 owns this guardrail.\n- When the Mobbin or Refero subscriptions are connected, they are an OPTIONAL real-world critique-against reference (via Code Mode) for naming the category default to deviate from, never a chooser and never copied. `references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md` owns the rules and `design_principles.md` stays the authority.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n**A design is ready when:**\n- ✅ The subject, audience, and the page's single job are named.\n- ✅ A token system (color, type, layout, signature) exists and was critiqued against the AI-default looks.\n- ✅ Every color and type decision derives from the revised plan.\n- ✅ The signature element is the one bold move, and everything else is quiet.\n- ✅ The quality floor holds: responsive, visible focus, reduced motion respected.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Related Skills\n\n- **`sk-code`** owns implementation. This skill decides the look, and sk-code builds it to the detected web surface's standards and verifies it.\n- **`sk-code-review`** can audit the built UI against the standards sk-code enforces.\n- **`mcp-chrome-devtools`** drives a real browser to screenshot the build for the self-critique step.\n- **`mcp-figma`** is the sibling transport to Figma Desktop. This skill's judgment applies whenever a Figma read or export feeds a design decision.\n- **Mobbin and Refero** (via Code Mode, `mobbin.*` / `refero.*`) are optional real-world UI reference libraries for naming the category's real-world default so a design can deviate from it deliberately. Read live, one reference, never a chooser, never copied. `references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md` owns the discipline.\n\n### Knowledge Base Dependencies\n\n**Required**: `references/design-process/design_principles.md`. **Conditional**: `sk-code` web-surface references for the target stack during implementation.\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router (Section 2) loads `references/design-process/design_principles.md` for every design task. Hand implementation to `sk-code`, use `mcp-chrome-devtools` for screenshot-based self-critique, and reach for `system-spec-kit` when the work needs packet documentation.\n\nUpstream: vendored from [anthropics/skills/skills/frontend-design](https://github.com/anthropics/skills/tree/main/skills/frontend-design) under Apache-2.0. `LICENSE.txt` carries the full terms.","lineStart":154,"lineEnd":215,"totalLines":215,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782489239778,"end":1782489239786}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_000a819dbc7a60d4016a3ea0979b608191b27dd8fe42ce520a"}},"id":"prt_f04a350a1001YvPOY5RqCgtXy6","sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","messageID":"msg_f04a2fe41001Lu07HMnpBISTsh"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782489239843,"sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CemGCY4fBXtumzDMQ7SzULZO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md","offset":265,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n265: ## 5. REFERENCES\n266: \n267: ### Core References\n268: \n269: - [`references/color/oklch_workflow.md`](references/color/oklch_workflow.md) - OKLCH conversion, palette generation, contrast, gamut, and review output.\n270: - [`references/color/palette_theming.md`](references/color/palette_theming.md) - Color dosage, semantic roles, tinted neutrals, surface scales, and dark mode.\n271: - [`references/type/typography_system.md`](references/type/typography_system.md) - Type roles, scale, pairing, measure, hierarchy, and text checks.\n272: - [`references/layout/layout_responsive.md`](references/layout/layout_responsive.md) - Spacing, rhythm, hierarchy, grids, responsive adaptation, and input contexts.\n273: - [`references/corpus_map.md`](references/corpus_map.md) - Source traceability for the distilled corpus.\n274: \n275: ### Parent Shared Base\n276: \n277: Use, do not duplicate, the parent vocabulary:\n278: - `../shared/anti_slop_principles.md`\n279: - `../shared/design_token_vocabulary.md`\n280: - `../shared/cognitive_laws.md`\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n285: \n286: - Color tokens have OKLCH values or a deliberate compatibility reason, semantic names, contrast evidence, and dark-mode behavior when needed.\n287: - Typography has role-based sizes, pairing rationale, line-height and measure constraints, and data/text utility guidance.\n288: - Layout uses a consistent spacing scale, clear grouping, visible hierarchy, and content-driven responsive behavior.\n289: - The final handoff is implementable by `sk-code` without guessing token roles or breakpoint intent.\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n294: \n295: - `sk-design` routes static visual-system prompts here.\n296: - `interface` supplies the distinctive direction this skill systematizes.\n297: - `motion` consumes static tokens when defining motion materials and interaction states.\n298: - `audit` scores the result for accessibility, performance, responsiveness, theming, and anti-slop risk.\n299: - `sk-code` implements the token system in the detected stack.\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n304: \n305: Manual validation scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`. The initial release notes are in `changelog/v1.0.0.0.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 305 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [`references/color/oklch_workflow.md`](references/color/oklch_workflow.md) - OKLCH conversion, palette generation, contrast, gamut, and review output.\n- [`references/color/palette_theming.md`](references/color/palette_theming.md) - Color dosage, semantic roles, tinted neutrals, surface scales, and dark mode.\n- [`references/type/typography_system.md`](references/type/typography_system.md) - Type roles, scale, pairing, measure, hierarchy, and text checks.\n- [`references/layout/layout_responsive.md`](references/layout/layout_responsive.md) - Spacing, rhythm, hierarchy, grids, responsive adaptation, and input contexts.\n- [`references/corpus_map.md`](references/corpus_map.md) - Source traceability for the distilled corpus.\n\n### Parent Shared Base\n\nUse, do not duplicate, the parent vocabulary:\n- `../shared/anti_slop_principles.md`\n- `../shared/design_token_vocabulary.md`\n- `../shared/cognitive_laws.md`\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md","text":"## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [`references/color/oklch_workflow.md`](references/color/oklch_workflow.md) - OKLCH conversion, palette generation, contrast, gamut, and review output.\n- [`references/color/palette_theming.md`](references/color/palette_theming.md) - Color dosage, semantic roles, tinted neutrals, surface scales, and dark mode.\n- [`references/type/typography_system.md`](references/type/typography_system.md) - Type roles, scale, pairing, measure, hierarchy, and text checks.\n- [`references/layout/layout_responsive.md`](references/layout/layout_responsive.md) - Spacing, rhythm, hierarchy, grids, responsive adaptation, and input contexts.\n- [`references/corpus_map.md`](references/corpus_map.md) - Source traceability for the distilled corpus.\n\n### Parent Shared Base\n\nUse, do not duplicate, the parent vocabulary:\n- `../shared/anti_slop_principles.md`\n- `../shared/design_token_vocabulary.md`\n- `../shared/cognitive_laws.md`\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- Color tokens have OKLCH values or a deliberate compatibility reason, semantic names, contrast evidence, and dark-mode behavior when needed.\n- Typography has role-based sizes, pairing rationale, line-height and measure constraints, and data/text utility guidance.\n- Layout uses a consistent spacing scale, clear grouping, visible hierarchy, and content-driven responsive behavior.\n- The final handoff is implementable by `sk-code` without guessing token roles or breakpoint intent.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n- `sk-design` routes static visual-system prompts here.\n- `interface` supplies the distinctive direction this skill systematizes.\n- `motion` consumes static tokens when defining motion materials and interaction states.\n- `audit` scores the result for accessibility, performance, responsiveness, theming, and anti-slop risk.\n- `sk-code` implements the token system in the detected stack.\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nManual validation scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`. The initial release notes are in `changelog/v1.0.0.0.md`.","lineStart":265,"lineEnd":305,"totalLines":305,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782489239830,"end":1782489239842}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_000a819dbc7a60d4016a3ea0979b708191ba3bbcc00adacb2d"}},"id":"prt_f04a350ff001T8AwBIdL7D2qf2","sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","messageID":"msg_f04a2fe41001Lu07HMnpBISTsh"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782489239925,"sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FcUFitQz1ruesGcxUloc5rJ9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md","offset":285,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n285: ## 5. REFERENCES\n286: \n287: ### Core References\n288: \n289: - [`references/motion_strategy.md`](references/motion_strategy.md) - Purpose, timing, easing, staging, principles, and motion materials.\n290: - [`references/micro_interactions.md`](references/micro_interactions.md) - Feedback, loading, gestures, delight, sound boundaries, and morphing icons.\n291: - [`references/animate_presence_patterns.md`](references/animate_presence_patterns.md) - `motion/react` and `AnimatePresence` patterns.\n292: - [`references/performance_reduced_motion.md`](references/performance_reduced_motion.md) - Performance, FLIP, scroll, layers, blur/filter, and reduced-motion guidance.\n293: - [`references/corpus_map.md`](references/corpus_map.md) - Source traceability for the distilled corpus.\n294: \n295: ### Parent Shared Base\n296: \n297: Use, do not duplicate, the parent references for shared vocabulary:\n298: - `../shared/anti_slop_principles.md`\n299: - `../shared/design_token_vocabulary.md`\n300: - `../shared/cognitive_laws.md`\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n305: \n306: - Every motion choice has a purpose and an affected state.\n307: - Timing, easing, and material choices are explicit.\n308: - Reduced-motion behavior is specified.\n309: - Implementation handoff names the target states, target properties, and verification risks.\n310: - Motion does not block interaction, compete with primary hierarchy, or exhaust the user.\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n315: \n316: - `sk-design` routes motion-family prompts here.\n317: - `interface` defines the visual story this child choreographs.\n318: - `foundations` supplies static tokens and layout constraints.\n319: - `audit` uses this skill's rules when scoring motion performance and accessibility.\n320: - `sk-code` implements motion in the target stack.\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n325: \n326: Manual validation scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`. The initial release notes are in `changelog/v1.0.0.0.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 326 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [`references/motion_strategy.md`](references/motion_strategy.md) - Purpose, timing, easing, staging, principles, and motion materials.\n- [`references/micro_interactions.md`](references/micro_interactions.md) - Feedback, loading, gestures, delight, sound boundaries, and morphing icons.\n- [`references/animate_presence_patterns.md`](references/animate_presence_patterns.md) - `motion/react` and `AnimatePresence` patterns.\n- [`references/performance_reduced_motion.md`](references/performance_reduced_motion.md) - Performance, FLIP, scroll, layers, blur/filter, and reduced-motion guidance.\n- [`references/corpus_map.md`](references/corpus_map.md) - Source traceability for the distilled corpus.\n\n### Parent Shared Base\n\nUse, do not duplicate, the parent references for shared vocabulary:\n- `../shared/anti_slop_principles.md`\n- `../shared/design_token_vocabulary.md`\n- `../shared/cognitive_laws.md`\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md","text":"## 5. REFERENCES\n\n### Core References\n\n- [`references/motion_strategy.md`](references/motion_strategy.md) - Purpose, timing, easing, staging, principles, and motion materials.\n- [`references/micro_interactions.md`](references/micro_interactions.md) - Feedback, loading, gestures, delight, sound boundaries, and morphing icons.\n- [`references/animate_presence_patterns.md`](references/animate_presence_patterns.md) - `motion/react` and `AnimatePresence` patterns.\n- [`references/performance_reduced_motion.md`](references/performance_reduced_motion.md) - Performance, FLIP, scroll, layers, blur/filter, and reduced-motion guidance.\n- [`references/corpus_map.md`](references/corpus_map.md) - Source traceability for the distilled corpus.\n\n### Parent Shared Base\n\nUse, do not duplicate, the parent references for shared vocabulary:\n- `../shared/anti_slop_principles.md`\n- `../shared/design_token_vocabulary.md`\n- `../shared/cognitive_laws.md`\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- Every motion choice has a purpose and an affected state.\n- Timing, easing, and material choices are explicit.\n- Reduced-motion behavior is specified.\n- Implementation handoff names the target states, target properties, and verification risks.\n- Motion does not block interaction, compete with primary hierarchy, or exhaust the user.\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n- `sk-design` routes motion-family prompts here.\n- `interface` defines the visual story this child choreographs.\n- `foundations` supplies static tokens and layout constraints.\n- `audit` uses this skill's rules when scoring motion performance and accessibility.\n- `sk-code` implements motion in the target stack.\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nManual validation scenarios live in `manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md`. The initial release notes are in `changelog/v1.0.0.0.md`.","lineStart":285,"lineEnd":326,"totalLines":326,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782489239916,"end":1782489239925}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_000a819dbc7a60d4016a3ea0979b7