{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782489240090,"sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_XH2fjDmNXf35RbkECQsk9Ygt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md","offset":84,"limit":26},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n84: ### Resource Domains\n85: \n86: The router discovers knowledge from a single root domain — this skill's `references/` directory: eight reference docs covering the v3 format spec and writing-style guide, the colour and component taxonomies, anti-patterns, the quality checklist, and the operational extraction-workflow and troubleshooting guides. Examples under `references/examples/` are study artifacts, not resources.\n87: \n88: ```text\n89: references/design_md_format.md    # v3 Style Reference section specification\n90: references/writing_style_guide.md    # voice, tone, section composition rules\n91: references/color_role_taxonomy.md    # color role naming + classification\n92: references/component_taxonomy.md     # component naming + hierarchy patterns\n93: references/anti_patterns.md          # common DESIGN.md mistakes to avoid\n94: references/quality_checklist.md      # pre-validate self-check\n95: references/extraction_workflow.md    # three-phase workflow, invocations, handoff\n96: references/troubleshooting.md        # failure modes and fixes\n97: references/examples/{stripe,vercel,linear,supabase}/  # gold-standard DESIGN.md + tokens.json pairs\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Resource Loading Levels\n101: \n102: | Level       | When to Load                         | Resources                                                                 |\n103: | ----------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n104: | ALWAYS      | Every invocation                     | `references/design_md_format.md`, `references/writing_style_guide.md`, `assets/cardinal_rules_card.md` (pre-write fabrication gate) |\n105: | CONDITIONAL | EXTRACT_WRITE intent                 | `references/color_role_taxonomy.md`, `references/component_taxonomy.md`, `references/anti_patterns.md` |\n106: | CONDITIONAL | VALIDATE / completion claim          | `references/quality_checklist.md`, `references/anti_patterns.md`  |\n107: | CONDITIONAL | STUDY intent                         | `references/examples/` (one site at a time, loaded as reference pairs)           |\n108: | ON_DEMAND   | Deep format edge-cases or component patterns | `references/anti_patterns.md`, `references/component_taxonomy.md` |\n109: \n\n(Showing lines 84-109 of 436. Use offset=110 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### Resource Domains\n\nThe router discovers knowledge from a single root domain — this skill's `references/` directory: eight reference docs covering the v3 format spec and writing-style guide, the colour and component taxonomies, anti-patterns, the quality checklist, and the operational extraction-workflow and troubleshooting guides. Examples under `references/examples/` are study artifacts, not resources.\n\n```text\nreferences/design_md_format.md    # v3 Style Reference section specification\nreferences/writing_style_guide.md    # voice, tone, section composition rules\nreferences/color_role_taxonomy.md    # color role naming + classification\nreferences/component_taxonomy.md     # component naming + hierarchy patterns\nreferences/anti_patterns.md          # common DESIGN.md mistakes to avoid\nreferences/quality_checklist.md      # pre-validate self-check\nreferences/extraction_workflow.md    # three-phase workflow, invocations, handoff\nreferences/troubleshooting.md        # failure modes and fixes\nreferences/examples/{stripe,vercel,linear,supabase}/  # gold-standard DESIGN.md + tokens.json pairs\n```\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load                         | Resources                                                                 |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md","text":"### Resource Domains\n\nThe router discovers knowledge from a single root domain — this skill's `references/` directory: eight reference docs covering the v3 format spec and writing-style guide, the colour and component taxonomies, anti-patterns, the quality checklist, and the operational extraction-workflow and troubleshooting guides. Examples under `references/examples/` are study artifacts, not resources.\n\n```text\nreferences/design_md_format.md    # v3 Style Reference section specification\nreferences/writing_style_guide.md    # voice, tone, section composition rules\nreferences/color_role_taxonomy.md    # color role naming + classification\nreferences/component_taxonomy.md     # component naming + hierarchy patterns\nreferences/anti_patterns.md          # common DESIGN.md mistakes to avoid\nreferences/quality_checklist.md      # pre-validate self-check\nreferences/extraction_workflow.md    # three-phase workflow, invocations, handoff\nreferences/troubleshooting.md        # failure modes and fixes\nreferences/examples/{stripe,vercel,linear,supabase}/  # gold-standard DESIGN.md + tokens.json pairs\n```\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level       | When to Load                         | Resources                                                                 |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| ALWAYS      | Every invocation                     | `references/design_md_format.md`, `references/writing_style_guide.md`, `assets/cardinal_rules_card.md` (pre-write fabrication gate) |\n| CONDITIONAL | EXTRACT_WRITE intent                 | `references/color_role_taxonomy.md`, `references/component_taxonomy.md`, `references/anti_patterns.md` |\n| CONDITIONAL | VALIDATE / completion claim          | `references/quality_checklist.md`, `references/anti_patterns.md`  |\n| CONDITIONAL | STUDY intent                         | `references/examples/` (one site at a time, loaded as reference pairs)           |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Deep format edge-cases or component patterns | `references/anti_patterns.md`, `references/component_taxonomy.md` |\n","lineStart":84,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":436,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782489240087,"end":1782489240090}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_000a819dbc7a60d4016a3ea0979b888191b68871f340b51585"}},"id":"prt_f04a35214001aStIO2RcWdvFtc","sessionID":"ses_0fb69c455ffeP1OgZTdo3RBP1U","messageID":"msg_f04a2fe41001Lu07HMnpBISTsh"}}
